definitions.definition: With respect to another set , a set such that each of the elements of the other set is also an element of the set.
Two or more different physical exercises performed back to back (i.e., without a period of rest between them). The exercises may employ the same muscle group, or opposing muscle groups.

main_definition: ( set theory ) (symbol: ⊇ ) With respect to another set , a set such that each of the elements of the other set is also an element of the set.
secondary_definitions: ( weightlifting ) Two or more different physical exercises performed back to back (i.e., without a period of rest between them). The exercises may employ the same muscle group, or opposing muscle groups.
